NewSUBARU
- Pile-up (Poisson-fitting) method for incident photon
flux
- Direct neutron multiplicity sorting with FED
DAQ: 8-channel APU8002 MCA in list mode used to record
timestamps and ring distribution of detected neutrons,
and energy and time stamps of photons detected by
monitor NaI.
Two neutron detection systems: (A) FED -
constant efficiency 4pi neutron detection
system, consisting of 31 3He proportional
counters arranged in three concentric rings
and embedded in a 46x46x50 cm3 polyethylene
moderator. (B) HED - high efficiency 4pi
neutron detection system, consisting of 20 3He
proportional counters arranged in three
concentric rings and embedded in a 36x36x50
cm3 polyethylene moderator.
8``x12`` NaI(Tl) detector for LCS beam flux
measurement
3.5``x4.0`` LaBr3(Ce) detector to determine the
energy profiles of the produced gamma-ray beams
